cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the evolution of natural languages and uses computational methods to generate conjectures about contacts between linguistic communities.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses computational methods such as answer set programming and constraint logic programming to model the evolution of languages.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper deals with the evolution of a family of languages, which can be seen as a type of learning process.
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper deals with the generation of conjectures about contacts between linguistic communities, which can be seen as a type of data management problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the computational complexity of generating plausible conjectures about contacts between prehistoric linguistic communities.
